  "notes": "Piedmontese. Gallo-Italic language of Piedmont, NW Italy. ~1.6 million speakers. Key features: (1) Front rounded vowels /y, ø/ (Gallo-Romance innovation). (2) Degemination. (3) Final vowel reduction/loss. (4) Nasal vowels. (5) Stronger intervocalic lenition than standard Italian. French adstrate influence due to historical Savoyard ties (Berruto 1974, Loporcaro 2009).",
